devdoc.author: Billy Rennekamp - <billy@gnosis.pm>

constructor.details: Constructor function sets initial storage of contract.

depositEther().details: Only owner can deposit contract Ether into the DutchX as WETH

depositToken(address,uint256).details: Only owner can deposit token to the DutchX

params.amount: The amount of token to deposit.
params.token: The token address that is being deposited.

dutchOpportunity(address,uint256).details: Executes a trade opportunity on dutchX. Assumes that there is a balance of WETH already on the dutchX

params.amount: Amount of Ether to use in arbitrage.
params.arbToken: Address of the token that should be arbitraged.

dutchOpportunity(address,uint256).return: Returns if transaction can be executed.

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

transferEther(uint256).details: Only owner can transfer any Ether currently in the contract to the owner address.

params.amount: The amount of Ether to withdraw

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

transferToken(address,uint256).details: Only owner can transfer tokens to the owner that belong to this contract

params.amount: The amount of token to transfer.
params.token: The token address that is being transferred.

uniswapOpportunity(address,uint256).details: Executes a trade opportunity on uniswap.

params.amount: Amount of Ether to use in arbitrage.
params.arbToken: Address of the token that should be arbitraged.

uniswapOpportunity(address,uint256).return: Returns if transaction can be executed.

withdrawEther(uint256).details: Only owner function to withdraw WETH from the DutchX, convert it to Ether and keep it in contract

params.amount: The amount of WETH to withdraw and convert.

withdrawEtherThenTransfer(uint256).details: Only owner can withdraw WETH from DutchX, convert to Ether and transfer to owner

params.amount: The amount of Ether to withdraw

withdrawToken(address,uint256).details: Only owner can withdraw a token from the DutchX

params.amount: The amount of token to withdraw. Can be larger than available balance and maximum will be withdrawn.
params.token: The token address that is being withdrawn.

withdrawToken(address,uint256).return: Returns the amount actually withdrawn from the DutchX

devdoc.title: Uniswap Arbitrage Module - Executes arbitrage transactions between Uniswap and DutchX.

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
